  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA371-kiḷavi">itu viṉaimuṟṟi maṟuttarāniṉṟāṉ pākaṟkuc colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is what he who was turning back after the work was completed said to the charioteer.</p>
        </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA371">
<l>            kāyāṅ kuṉṟattuk koṉṟai pōla</l>
<l>            māmalai viṭarakam viḷaṅka miṉṉi</l>
<l>            māyō ḷirunta tēe nōkki</l>
<l>            viyaliru vicumpakam putaiyap pāayp</l>
<l>            peyaṟuṭaṅ kiṉavē peyyā vāṉa</l>
<l>            niḻaṟikaḻ cuṭarttoṭi ñekiḻa vēṅki</l>
<l>            yaḻaṟuṭaṅ kiṉaḷē yāyiḻai yataṉetir</l>
<l>            kuḻaṟuṭaṅ kiṉarē kōvalar</l>
<l>            taḻaṅkukura lurumiṉ kaṅku lāṉē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent">            Flashing so that the insides of caves shine in the dark mountains,</l>
<l rend="indent2">            as a Laburnum tree on a hill with ironwood trees,</l>
<l rend="indent">            looking at the land where [my] dark one had been ,</l>
<l rend="indent">            spreading so that the inside of the wide dark sky is buried</l>
<l>        the unraining clouds have started to rain.</l>
<l rend="indent">            Lamenting for [her] glowing bracelets, glittering in the shade<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">niḻal tikaḻ</term>: T.V.G. reads here a special meaning of <term xml:lang="ta">niḻal</term> as "shining", and adduces parallels from Cint. 1325 and Parip. 3.51. But actually shade is perfectly comprehensible here: SHE is sitting in the dark coming with the rains, and when the flashes come, her bangles catch the light.</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent">            to become loose</l>
<l>        the [one of] choice jewels has started to cry.</l>
<l rend="indent4">            In the face of that<note place="foot">Actually, one would expect rather <term xml:lang="ta">ataṉṟalai</term> than <term xml:lang="ta">ataṉetir</term> here.</note></l>
<l>        the cowherds have started [to play their] flutes,</l>
<l rend="indent2">            in the night of thunder with resounding voice.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
